Enforces that every member crate in the workspace declares `[lints]` with `workspace = true` in its Cargo.toml; without this line, the workspace [workspace.lints] table applies no restrictions to that crate. The script fails CI if any real crate (one with a [package] table) is missing the declaration.

Manifests are enumerated via `git ls-files`, not filesystem walk, so the inspected set is a pure function of repo state and never races concurrent writes to target/. The check uses an awk state machine to confirm `workspace = true` appears inside the [lints] table specifically, not in [workspace] or any other section—the grep for [package] first filters out the virtual workspace root and non-package manifests. Exit code is 0 if all member crates pass, 1 if any are missing the declaration.